Campus Counsel provides inhouse legal advice for UC Davis on matters large and small.  Matters they have advised on include negotiations with Sodexho, and neverending Howard Zochlinski case.  Steve Drown is the head lawyer in the Campus Counsel office.

If wikizens would like to request information from the university that some lowerlevel official denied you, contact Lynnette Temple.  She handles information requests under the wiki:wikipedia:Freedom of Information Act (United States) Freedom of Information Act and the http://www.google.com/search?qCalifornia+Public+Records+Act California Public Records Act.

They are located on the second floor of Mrak Hall.  The office entrance is fairly unwelcoming  there are chairs in a tiny waiting room, and you cant even talk to a person inside unless they come out to speak to you.  Charming.
